  "texts": [
    "However, for most prevalence levels, it has a flat trend, and there is a lot of fluctuations at low prevalence.",
    "This can be understood from its alternative expression",
    ", where the diverging trends of TPR and TNR compete with each other.",
    "Here is a summary of the above results.",
    "As TPR, TNR, PPV and NPV mostly concern prediction accuracy for one class only, they have a close to monotonic relationship with prevalence in either the positive or negative direction though PPV and NPV fluctuate much more."
